{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"42d6e335-c784-463f-9488-4310505b925e","content":"No files found in the working directory — so here's exactly how to do it:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to the XAML root\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is:\n- Add the `xmlns:vm` namespace pointing to your ViewModel's CLR namespace.\n- Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the `<ContentPage>` element (or on any inner element to scope it).\n\nEvery `{Binding}` under that element is now **compiled** — the compiler resolves property names against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit **build errors** (not warnings) for typos or missing properties. To make this even stricter:\n\n**a) Enable `TrimMode` and treat warnings as errors** in your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n  <!-- Optionally promote all warnings to errors: -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**b) Verify it works** — intentionally misspell a property:\n```xml\n<Label Text=\"{Binding Themee}\" />   <!-- build error: property not found -->\n```\n\n### 3. Important caveats\n\n| Scenario | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| DataTemplate with a different type | Add `x:DataType=\"vm:OtherType\"` on the `DataTemplate` |\n| Need to opt-out for one binding | Use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on that element |\n| BindingContext set in code-behind | Still works — `x:DataType` only affects compile-time checking |\n\nThat's it. No runtime reflection, earlier error detection, and slightly better performance.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e9381a12-e580-43c2-9e03-18b93d5f08e0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking a general question about how to convert a MAUI page to use compiled bindings. Let me provide guidance since there are no actual files to modify.","outputTokens":671,"requestId":"980E:18EF48:1558D62:17E2969:6A051DAA"},"id":"35cf5bfc-ab6e-440f-988c-1b92828246d2","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:56:24.963Z","parentId":"74b30834-1c0f-48bc-9469-8b299e401630"}
